# Abo Shalbak — Environment Variables
#
# Copy to `.env` in the repo root (or `backend/.env`).

## Development

```env
# Server
PORT=5000
HOST=127.0.0.1
NODE_ENV=development

# Security (REQUIRED in production)
JWT_SECRET=change-me-to-a-long-random-string-at-least-32-chars
JWT_EXPIRES_IN=8h

# CORS — comma-separated allowed origins (empty in production = same-origin only)
# ALLOWED_ORIGINS=http://127.0.0.1:3001,http://127.0.0.1:3002

# Database
DATABASE_PATH=./data/supermarket.db

# Backups (stored outside public folders)
BACKUP_DIR=./backups

# Telegram — refund approval bot (BotFather #1)
TELEGRAM_REFUND_BOT_TOKEN=
TELEGRAM_REFUND_WEBHOOK_SECRET=

# Telegram — expiry alerts bot (BotFather #2)
TELEGRAM_EXPIRY_BOT_TOKEN=

# Refund approval bot -> refunds group
TELEGRAM_REFUND_CHAT_ID=
# Expiry alerts bot -> expiration group
TELEGRAM_EXPIRY_CHAT_ID=
# Optional fallback used if either of the above is empty
TELEGRAM_MANAGER_CHAT_ID=

# Local dev: set to 1 so Approve/Reject buttons work without HTTPS webhook
TELEGRAM_USE_POLLING=1

# Daily expiry alert hour (0-23, default 8). Set DISABLE_EXPIRY_TELEGRAM_ALERT=1 to disable.
TELEGRAM_EXPIRY_ALERT_HOUR=8
# Fallback if expiry_alert_days is not set in store settings
TELEGRAM_EXPIRY_DAYS=7
```

## Production (Docker — store PC on LAN)

```env
NODE_ENV=production
PORT=3000
HOST=0.0.0.0

# REQUIRED — generate a long random string (32+ chars). Never use defaults in production.
JWT_SECRET=your-long-random-secret-here

DATABASE_PATH=/app/data/supermarket.db
BACKUP_DIR=/app/backups

# Optional — same-origin deployment usually needs no CORS; set if accessing from another origin
# ALLOWED_ORIGINS=http://192.168.1.10:3000

# Telegram — LAN store can use polling (no HTTPS required)
TELEGRAM_USE_POLLING=1
TELEGRAM_REFUND_BOT_TOKEN=
TELEGRAM_REFUND_WEBHOOK_SECRET=
TELEGRAM_EXPIRY_BOT_TOKEN=
TELEGRAM_REFUND_CHAT_ID=
TELEGRAM_EXPIRY_CHAT_ID=
TELEGRAM_MANAGER_CHAT_ID=
TELEGRAM_EXPIRY_ALERT_HOUR=8
```

## Production checklist (shop PC)

1. Set `NODE_ENV=production` and a strong unique `JWT_SECRET`
2. Set static IP on the store PC (e.g. `192.168.1.10`)
3. Run `docker compose up -d`
4. Open Admin: `http://192.168.1.10:3000/admin`
5. Open POS: `http://192.168.1.10:3000/pos`
6. Change default seeded passwords on first login
7. Ensure `backups/` and `data/` are not web-accessible (they are mounted volumes, not served)

For remote phone access via Tailscale, see [DEPLOY-TAILSCALE.md](./DEPLOY-TAILSCALE.md).
